    <p>Software pricing is a complex and tricky topic. The price of a software product depends on a variety of factors
        such as development costs, competition, regional specifics, and others. There are 3 major pricing strategies
        that can be used to estimate your plugin price. It is recommended to consider all 3 approaches:
    </p>
    <list>
            <li>
                <b>
                    <a href="cost-plus-pricing.topic">Cost-plus pricing</a>
                </b>
                can be used as a benchmark to validate the lowest price that you can consider.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>
                    <a href="competitor-based-pricing.topic">Competitor-based pricing</a>
                </b>
                allows you to find out what competitors are charging.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>
                    <a href="value-based-pricing.topic">Value-based pricing</a>
                </b>
                helps understand the maximum price customers are ready to pay.
            </li>
        </list>

</topic>